<p>I'm using JQuery Mobile with it's mobile themed datepicker plugin. Here is the relevant code, as per JQuery Mobile Datepicker demo, that works just as expected:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;head&gt; &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"&gt; &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.css"/&gt; &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="jquery.mobile.icons.min.css" /&gt; &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"/&gt; &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="jquery.mobile.datepicker.css"/&gt; &lt;script src="jquery-1.11.3.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script&gt;     //reset type=date inputs to text     $( document ).bind( "mobileinit", function(){         $.mobile.page.prototype.options.degradeInputs.date = true;     });  &lt;/script&gt; &lt;script src="jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script src="jquery.ui.datepicker.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script id="mobile-datepicker" src="jquery.mobile.datepicker.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;/head&gt;  &lt;body&gt;   &lt;input id="servicedate" name="servicedate" data-role="date" type="text" /&gt; &lt;/body&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Above produces properly styled mobile datepicker tied to "servicedate" input like <a href="http://i58.tinypic.com/mbk37q.jpg" rel="nofollow">this</a>.</p>  <p>Now, any attempt to interact with datepicker, like dynamically changing any of the options, causes it to lose its mobile style. To the bottom of body, I add a:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;script&gt;   $("#servicedate").datepicker({ dateFormat: "DD, MM dd yy", });  &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>... and it now, while option does work, produces rather unpleasant looking, un-themed datepicker like <a href="http://i62.tinypic.com/vnhy10.jpg" rel="nofollow">this</a>.</p>  <p>Any help/guidance with what I am doing wrong would be appreciated. Thanks.</p>